    • Method Detail

      • register

        <L extends Listener> void register(java.lang.Class<L> type,
                                   Resource<? super L> resource)
        Registers a resource with the given listener type. Resource registration hooks are properly invoked during the registration process.

        Note that this method propagates any exception thrown by the specified resource as a cause of a ResourceRegistrationException instance.

        Parameters:
        type - the listener type with which the specified resource is to be registered, not null
        resource - the resource to be registered with the specified listener type, not null
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified resource implementation does not support the specified listener type
        ResourceAlreadyRegistredException - if the specified listener type and resource pair is already registered and this resource manager panics
        ResourceRegistrationException - if an exception is thrown by the specified resource during the registration process
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either of listener type or resource is null

      • unregister

        <L extends Listener> void unregister(java.lang.Class<L> type,
                                     Resource<? super L> resource)
        Unregisters a resource with the given listener type. Resource unregistration hooks are properly invoked during the unregistration process.

        Note that this method propagates any exception thrown by the specified resource as a cause of a ResourceUnregistrationException instance.

        Parameters:
        type - the listener type with which the specified resource is to be unregistered, not null
        resource - the resource to be unregistered from the specified listener type, not null
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified resource implementation does not support the specified listener type
        ResourceNotRegistredException - if the specified listener type and resource pair is not registered and this resource manager panics
        ResourceUnregistrationException - if an exception is thrown by the specified resource during the unregistration process
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either of listener type or resource is null

      • unregisterAll

        <L extends Listener> void unregisterAll(java.lang.Class<L> type)
        Unregisters all resources assignable to the specified listener type. A resource is assignable to a given listener type if the listener type supported by the resource is assignable to the given listener type. Resource unregistration hooks are properly invoked for all matched resources during the unregistration process.

        Note that this method collects all exceptions thrown by resources during the unregistration process and propagates them as suppressed exceptions of a ResourceUnregistrationException instance.

        Parameters:
        type - the listener type to which the assignable resources are going be unregistered, not null
        Throws:
        ResourceUnregistrationException - if an exception is thrown by one or more resources during the unregistration process
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified listener type is null

      • assignables

        <L extends Listener> java.util.Set<Resource<? extends L>> assignables(java.lang.Class<L> type)
        Returns a set of resources assignable to the specified listener type.

        A resource is assignable to a given listener type if the listener type supported by the resource is assignable to the given listener type.

      • registrables

        <L extends Listener> java.util.Set<Resource<? super L>> registrables(java.lang.Class<L> type)
        Returns a set of resources registrable with the specified listener type.

        A resource is registrable with a given listener type if the listener type supported by the resource is equal to the given listener type or one of its superinterfaces.

      • registrations

        com.google.common.collect.SetMultimap<java.lang.Class<? extends Listener>,Resource<?>> registrations()
        Returns a set multimap of listener types to all registered resources.

                   Resource<?> resource)
        Determines whether the specified resource is registered with the specified listener type by this resource manager.
        Parameters:

        Returns:

        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either of listener type or resource is null
